3
1 (4) Training coordination.
2 (5) Other costs associated with clinical instruction.
3 (d) The state department shall verify compliance with this
4 section and the reporting requirements under section 7 of this
5 chapter. If the state department determines that a nonprofit
6 hospital is not complying with this section, the state department
7 may require the nonprofit hospital to submit a corrective action
8 plan to the state department. If a nonprofit hospital continues to
9 violate this section, the state department may take action under
10 section 8 of this chapter.
11 SECTION 6. IC 16-21-9-7, AS AMENDED BY P.L.6-2012,
12 SECTION 115, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS
13 [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 7. (a) Each nonprofit hospital shall
14 prepare an annual report of the community benefits plan. The report
15 must include, in addition to the community benefits plan itself, the
16 following background information:
17 (1) The hospital's mission statement.
18 (2) A disclosure of the health care needs of the community that
19 were considered in developing the hospital's community benefits
20 plan.
21 (3) A disclosure of the amount and types of community benefits
22 actually provided, including charity care. Charity care must be
23 reported as a separate item from other community benefits.
24 (4) Verification of compliance with the preceptor requirement
25 under section 4(b) of this chapter, including the following
26 information concerning preceptor activities:
27 (A) The number of clinical departments.
28 (B) A list of departments meeting the preceptor
29 requirement.
30 (C) Expenditures associated with the operation of a
31 preceptor.
32 (5) The nonprofit hospital's expenditure for each of the
33 following categories of community benefits:
34 (A) Charity care.
35 (B) Government sponsored indigent health care.
36 (C) Donations.
37 (D) Education, including preceptor activities.
38 (E) Government sponsored program services.
39 (F) Research.
40 (G) Subsidized health services.
41 (6) The nonprofit hospital's total community benefits
42 expenditure.
