14 (b) Each nonprofit hospital shall annually file a report of the
15 community benefits plan with the state department. For a hospital's
16 fiscal year that ends before July 1, 2011, the report must be filed not
17 later than one hundred twenty (120) days after the close of the
18 hospital's fiscal year. For a hospital's fiscal year that ends after June 30,
19 2011, the report must be filed at the same time the nonprofit hospital
20 files its annual return described under Section 6033 of the Internal
21 Revenue Code that is timely filed under Section 6072(e) of the Internal
22 Revenue Code, including any applicable extension authorized under
23 Section 6081 of the Internal Revenue Code.
24 (c) Each nonprofit hospital shall post the report on the nonprofit
25 hospital's website and prepare a statement that notifies the public that
26 the annual report of the community benefits plan is:
27 (1) public information;
28 (2) filed with the state department; and
29 (3) available to the public on the nonprofit hospital's website
30 and that a written copy will be provided to the public by the
31 nonprofit hospital upon request. from the state department.
32 This statement shall be posted in prominent places throughout the
33 hospital, including the emergency room waiting area and the
34 admissions office waiting area. The statement shall also be printed in
35 the hospital patient guide or other material that provides the patient
36 with information about the admissions criteria of the hospital.
37 (d) Each nonprofit hospital shall develop a written notice about any
38 charity care program operated by the hospital and how to apply for
39 charity care. The notice must be in appropriate languages if possible.
40 The notice must also be conspicuously posted in the following areas:
41 (1) The general waiting area.
42 (2) The waiting area for emergency services.
