19 SECTION 7. IC 16-21-9-8 IS AMENDED TO READ AS
20 FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 8. (a) The state
21 department may assess a civil penalty against a nonprofit hospital that
22 fails to do the following:
23 (1) Comply with section 4 of this chapter.
24 (2) Make a report of the community benefits plan as required
25 under this chapter.
26 (3) Otherwise comply with this chapter.
27 (b) For a violation of subsection (a)(1) or (a)(3), the state
28 department may take any of the following actions:
29 (1) Require the nonprofit hospital to submit a corrective
30 action plan.
31 (2) Impose a civil penalty in an amount not to exceed ten
32 thousand dollars ($10,000) per violation if the nonprofit
33 hospital:
34 (A) fails to submit a corrective action plan;
35 (B) fails to comply with the corrective action plan; or
36 (C) continuously violates subsection (a)(1) or (a)(3).
37 A penalty imposed under this subsection shall be deposited in the
38 state general fund.
39 (c) For a violation of subsection (a)(2), the penalty may not exceed
40 one thousand dollars ($1,000) for each day a report is delinquent after
41 the date on which the report is due. No penalty may be assessed against
42 a hospital under this section subsection until thirty (30) business days
